---
import AcademicLayout from '../layouts/AcademicLayout.astro';

const title = 'Terms of Use & Liability Disclaimer';
const abstract =
  'By reading this highly scientific analysis, you agree to not sue us when you realize your entire career is built on a deprecated framework.';
---

<AcademicLayout title={title} abstract={abstract}>
  <section>
    <h2>1. Data Collection</h2>
    <p>
      We collect precisely zero personal data from you. This is a static site. We don't want your
      cookies, your email, or your long-winded opinions on why your obscure tech stack is actually
      "poised for a comeback."
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Algorithmic Brutality</h2>
    <p>
      The "Deaditude" scores are calculated by cold, unfeeling scripts aggregating public data from
      the internet. If your favorite framework has a 95% Deaditude score, it is not a personal
      attack. The internet abandoned it, we just did the math. Please direct your anger at the
      original author who archived the repository in 2019 to "focus on their podcast."
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>
      The primary investigators of this research assume no legal responsibility if your CTO reads
      this site and forces a complete rewrite of your architecture. We are also not liable for any
      existential dread, imposter syndrome, or sudden urges to abandon software engineering and
      become a carpenter.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. Academic Integrity</h2>
    <p>
      While our metrics are drawn from real API endpoints and our math is computationally sound,
      this is ultimately an exercise in pointing at burning tech stacks and coping through sarcasm.
      Do not use this as the sole primary source in a serious enterprise technical evaluation. Or
      do. We're not your boss.
    </p>
  </section>
</AcademicLayout>
